<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🐼 M003 Extension — Build the Panda (Intermediate)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> 3D Panda (x, y, z) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Intermediate (Extension, after Week 6) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 40 minutes</p>
<p>Build a <strong>standing panda</strong> in 3D — white body, black ears, black eye patches, black legs. Every block needs <strong>three</strong> numbers <strong>(x, y, z)</strong>: x <strong>across</strong>, y <strong>up</strong>, z <strong>deeper</strong> (forward).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move your feet, move your panda.</p>
<p>🎨 White parts = <strong>white concrete</strong>. Black parts = <strong>black wool</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each set. Write a sentence for each.</p>
<pre><code>place black block at (2, 3, 1)
place black block at (2, 4, 1)
place black block at (2, 5, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only y changes. What happens to this leg?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place white block at (2, 8, 1)
place white block at (2, 8, 2)
place white block at (2, 8, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only z changes. What happens to the line?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place white block at (2, 7, 1)
place black block at (2, 7, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Same (x, y, z). What do you see, and why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Fix each one. Then say why it was wrong.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — This ear should sit one step <strong>deeper</strong>, at (2, 9, 2). It has only two numbers, so it lands flat on the front.</p>
<pre><code>place black block at (2, 9)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work? (1–2 sentences)</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — This eye should be <strong>up high on the front</strong>: (5, 7, 1). The last two numbers are swapped.</p>
<pre><code>place black block at (5, 1, 7)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work? (1–2 sentences)</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Look at the 🐼 panda in the world. Walk around it. Then build <strong>one full panda</strong> on your home spot — head, two ears, two eyes, two legs.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Front face</strong> (keep z = 1): fill a white head from (2, 5, 1) to (5, 8, 1). Add two black ears on top — (2, 9, 1) and (5, 9, 1). Add two black eyes — (2, 7, 1) and (5, 7, 1). Add two black legs at the bottom — fill (2, 3, 1) to (2, 4, 1) and (5, 3, 1) to (5, 4, 1).</p>
<p><strong>Add depth:</strong> build the white head again at z = 2, then z = 3, until your panda is as deep as the real one. Build the ears and legs deeper too.</p>
<p><strong>Face on front only:</strong> at z = 2 and z = 3, place plain white where the eyes were.</p>
<p>💡 Tip: the eyes only show on the <strong>front</strong>. The sides and back are plain white.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> — one take, no stopping (a phone is fine). Show these in order:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera at the panda. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
<p>The most fun part was ______.</p>
<p>Something new I learned was ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your <strong>one</strong> video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
